wikipedia_page.main: Alan Willey (16 September 1941 – 28 April 2017) was an English professional footballer who played for Bridgwater Town, Millwall and Oxford United. Having started out in football as a groundstaff boy for Exeter City, he signed for Bridgwater Town before moving to Oxford United for £300. He joined Millwall in 1966.
